To compile:

    gcc -Wall main.c -o example-if-else-statements

To run:

    ./example-if-else-statements

Output:

  example 1 -- inputting a positive number:

    Hello, please enter a number: 10
    You entered a positive number

  example 2 -- inputting a negative number:

    Hello, please enter a number: -3
    You entered a negative number

  example 3 -- inputting 0:

    Hello, please enter a number: 0
    You entered the value zero

  example 4 -- inputting 99:

    Hello, please enter a number: 99
    You entered a positive number
    I really like this number


